results.notes:
Asci dislodged in smash mount have lengths between 75 and 120, basal widths 3.5-5, and apical widths 4.5-7 microns. Most of them observed with lengths 75-95.
Spores 7-9 × 3.5-4.
Morphology (small thin regularly clavate fruit bodies) seems to favor N. vitellina.
Spore quotient (widths not exceeding 4 microns) favors N. vitellina.
Asci are significantly longer than what is reported for N. vitellina, some within the range of N. irregularis but many appear to be shorter than what is reported for N. irregularis.
A subsequent collection from the same location also had asci with length in the same range; longer than reported for N. vitellina obs 442157. Observation 442157 was sequenced; ITS and LSU determined N. vitellina.
